comments: Despite how often I caught myself drooling at him rather than taking notes, I learned a lot in this class. Lectures weren\'t always clear/totally organized, but he definitely knows what he\'s talking about. Talking outside of class is a huge help if you are having trouble. Smart/funny/cute teacher, interesting material. Hard not to love this class!
Amazing! I learned a lot and he always kept my attention.

I just took this class and I enjoyed it.Mr Delehanty\'s teaching style is informative and full of examples. The material is not easy by nature but he provided extra help along side class lectures so that concepts were made understandable. Nick\'s class is not an easy one, that\'s for sure. Actually, it\'s pretty tough. But he is hot.

first, i gotta say this guy is hot!!! as for the class, it is pretty heavy and you have to work to get a good grade. he is totally there for students who want to learn and try. that said, some of my friends who also took this class were disappointed it wasn\'t super easy...but they just wanted to freeload anyway, so i wouldn\'t pay attention to them.

Philosophy of Existentialism. This is probably the worst philosophy teacher I\'ve ever had. His lectures are extremely jumpy and unclear and so my notes are incomprehensible. He\'s more concerned with giving quizzes and tests than making sure his student can comprehend the material. I will never take another Philosophy class after this.
